Your team is bootstrapping an evaluation pipeline in Langfuse. As a first step, you need to programmatically create a versioned dataset and seed it with a small set of question/expected-answer items using the official TypeScript/JavaScript SDK (`@langfuse/client`). The created dataset will later be used to run experiments.

Langfuse is a multi-tenant cloud service shared across many test runs, so the dataset name must be scoped with the current `run-id` to avoid collisions between concurrent trials.

## Requirements
- Write a TypeScript program that uses the `@langfuse/client` package to talk to Langfuse Cloud.
- Create a dataset whose name is exactly `qa-dataset-${run-id}` where `run-id` is read from the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable.
